args:
Aspidochelone disappears into the space
between worlds, but the Syndicate is not
defeated—so Aldred sets out on a journey to
hunt them down. He and the prince agree to
help each other if it's ever needed, and they
set off on their separate ways.
Extraordinary. Even fused with\nAspidochelone, I find myself defeated...
Very well. I accept my loss—but know\nthis is not the end of the Syndicate!
Someday, you will know our terrible truth!\nGLORY TO THE SYNDICAAAAAATE...
We did it! We defeated Aspidochelone!
G-get away from me... I can't...\ncontrol the dragon's power...
This will not be forgiven,\nfoolish child of man.
No. I am the true ruler of this body—and I\nwill not forgive the humans who forced me\ninto such a weak and stunted vessel.
My name is Barbatos! Know my fury,\nand by it learn your own folly!
Aw, crap fire and save matches!
Well? What's the plan, boss?\nWe gonna fight this thing?
We can't—this dragon is also Aldred!
I killed my own sister.\nI can't come back from that.
If I were to kill you, too...\nPlease! Don't let my sins pile any higher!
No! The dragon is back in charge!
The time for destruction is at hand.\nNow accept your reward for toying\nwith my sacred body, humans!
We need a plan RIGHT NOW!
Your Highness, no! Do not approach him!
If you truly have your share of sins,\nAldred, that means you can't give up!
The only way to atone for your sins is to\ntake responsibility for them and LIVE!
Your voice can no longer reach him.\nNow learn regret for your foolishness.\nLearn it through your own deaths!
You are a stain that must be\ncleansed from this world!
I know how miserable it is that you brought\nharm to your sister, Aldred, but that's not\nthe crime you need to repent for!
Your crime is yielding your fate to this\ndragon! It's the weakness of your heart!
What you said about my crime being\na weakness of the heart, I mean.
I was wrong. Your heart's not weak at all.
No one with a weak heart would have\nbeen able to overcome that dragon.
No—I AM weak. Without all of you,\nI would have been consumed by it.
But I'll continue on. I'm going to accept\nbeing a sinner with weakness in his heart.
Because you taught me that's\nhow I can atone.
What will you two do now?
I'm going after the Syndicate. We may\nhave beaten the Doctor, but there are\nplenty more just like him still out there.
We'll find them and rip them out,\nroot and stem.
The Doctor said something about the true\npower of the Syndicate at the very end.

I know of a Syndicate boss who led a
major city guild, and I've heard rumors
they may have infiltrated the royal court
of the Empire itself.
The Doctor was just one man among many.
It's hard to believe such a massive\norganization kept itself a secret.
There must be a way for us to help.
I think you've already got your hands full\ntaking on the entire Empire, don't you?
Dammit! The Syndicate is mine,\nso stay the hell out of my way!
Aldred! Dude! You actually told a joke!\n...Did it hurt? You need to lie down?
I've never heard him do that before...
I DO have a sense of humor, you know!
Hee hee! Oh man, your face is SO red!
Hey, this is a good thing! Getting razzed\na bit means we've become pals.
It's a strange feeling. I haven't thought\nabout anything except revenge in so long...
You're the only reason I was\nable to take down the Doctor.
I did what I always do: I fought to protect\nwhat is important. It just happened that\nthe Doctor was my enemy this time.
So like I said, you don't owe me.
Well then, I'll make a promise...
If you ever need me in your fight,\nI'll be there.
I won't hesitate when the time comes!
I hope we can all meet again\nsomewhere down the line.
Thanks, everybody! See you soon, I hope!
He will need to bear the burden\nof his body forever.
It is a harsh fate indeed.
Yes, but he's not the type\nto let that get him down.
